.SH NAME
input_ff_create \- create force-feedback device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" input_ff_create
.BI "(struct input_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int max_effects "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
input device supporting force-feedback
.IP "max_effects" 12
maximum number of effects supported by the device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function allocates all necessary memory for a force feedback
portion of an input device and installs all default handlers.
\fIdev->ffbit\fP should be already set up before calling this function.
Once ff device is created you need to setup its upload, erase,
playback and other handlers before registering input device
